    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/4–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 17, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>898. <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> has qualified Soviet approval
                    of invitations to governmental international organizations to send unofficial
                    observers to San Francisco by the condition that no such observers be nationals
                    of countries not participating in the Conference.<note n="29" xml:id="d160fn1"
                        >At the third meeting of the Informal Organizing Group on April 13,
                        Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName> stated that he had
                        received new and specific instructions on this subject; see minutes of
                        meeting, <ref target="#pg_283">pp. 283</ref>, <ref target="#pg_285"
                            >285</ref>. Mr. <persName>Kapustin</persName> was informed by telephone
                        on April 17 that on that date <persName>Sean Lester</persName> was leaving
                        the United Kingdom as an official observer for the League of Nations and
                        that “objection to his coming would be a serious inconvenience”.
                        (500.CC/4–1745)</note> Your 999, April 1, <pb facs="0392" n="330"
                        xml:id="pg_330"/> 1 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d160fn2">See last portion of
                        footnote 22, <ref target="#pg_153">p. 153</ref>.</note> on basis of which
                    invitations had already gone out does not mention this qualification. Can you
                    have Foreign Office correct <persName corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName>’s
                    instructions? Please send us text of <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                        >Molotov</persName>’s March 31 note. The only case which has come to our
                    attention so far is that of <persName>Sean Lester</persName>, an Irish
                    national.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
